# Tailwind Styling

## Class Ordering

Order classes logically: layout → spacing → sizing → typography → colors → borders → effects.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<button className="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white bg-red-600 rounded-lg hover:bg-red-700">
  Analyze
</button>
```

## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first: base styles, then `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`.
- Use responsive utilities for layout and spacing.

```tsx
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
```

## Custom Values

- Prefer Tailwind utilities over arbitrary values when possible.
- Use `@apply` in CSS only for repeated patterns; otherwise use `className`.

## Design Tokens

- Define custom colors, fonts, and spacing in `tailwind.config.js`.
- Use semantic names: `primary`, `danger`, `muted`, not raw hex codes in components.

## Avoid

- Inline `style={{}}` unless dynamic values (e.g. `width: ${percent}%`).
- Long `className` strings — extract to a variable or component if >5 utilities.
- `!important` — fix specificity instead.
